About Dots and Boxes:
=====================

Detailed information about game can be found online at:
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dots_and_Boxes


Usage:
======
path/of/pydnb$ ./pydnb.py N
    - N: number of dots of the game

While vertical dots are indicated by numbers, horizontal ones are indicated by letters.
In order to draw a line you have to describe it with its two end points.

Example:
                                                                                                                              
         a      b      c      d                                                                                
                                                                                                                              
                                                                                                               
  0      *      *      *      *                                                                                
                |                                                                                              
                |                                                                                              
                |                                                                                             
  1      *      *      *      *                                                                                
                                                                                                               
The line above corresponds to 0b1b.


Known Issues:
=============
PyDnB uses curses library as user interface toolkit. It provides clear, 
useful environment for players, but after exiting the game the terminal window
behaves unexpectedly.



